The paper discusses the challenges related to wireless connectivity and security in the context of cellular-connected UAVs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses cyber-physical attacks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of artificial neural networks suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses UAV-enabled intelligent transportation systems, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses mobility management and handover, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
